[even] great devas are disturbed by =\r\nfear&quot;. Then how easy can it be for other beings, including members of =\r\nthis list, to &quot;remain without fear in the supreme state of non-duality=\r\n&quot;?&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nPlease don&#39;t get me wrong. I am not against adwaita =\r\nor non-duality at all, as those familiar with my writings should know by no=\r\nw. But I accept the fact that a huge majority of spiritual seekers are mean=\r\nt to remain in duality for many many more lives. A message other than &quot=\r\n;attain the supreme state of non-duality&quot; may be more useful to them a=\r\nt their current stage!&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=\r\n=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nA great cricket batsman may not make the greate=\r\nst coach. Hitting the ball may seem so easy to him and he may simply say, &=\r\nquot;look at the ball and hit it.&quot; That much instruction is certainly =\r\nnot enough for a budding player to start playing like that great player.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nAnother gifted coach may observe faults in the technique of the bu=\r\ndding player and give some tips. That may turn out to be more useful than t=\r\nhe inspiring words from the great player! Of course, no matter how good ins=\r\ntructions one gets, the budding player may not play like that great player =\r\nanytime soon! Nevertheless, his goal should be to keep improving!&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSome=\r\n great teachers, especially of the Adwaita philosophy, are like the great c=\r\nricket batsman in the above analogy. They tell you what is obvious and natu=\r\nral to *them*. Their words are very inspiring.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSome other teachers=\r\n fine-tune their message for an audience. They show a real path (instead of=\r\n a lofty target) using which one can start making progress. One may or may =\r\nnot reach a supreme state anytime soon, but one will start making progress.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nDifferent spiritual teachers come for different purposes. The role pl=\r\nayed by each one is important in its own right. Ramana maharshi was undoubt=\r\nedly a great master. However, when it comes to the second category of teach=\r\ners I mentioned above, one name that strikes to me instantly is that of Ram=\r\nakrishna Paramahamsa. He was a master at fine-tuning his message for the in=\r\ndividual. While most great masters were adepts in one path (jnaana yoga or =\r\nbhakti yoga or karma yoga or raja yoga), he was unique in that he experienc=\r\ned the supreme through each path and was equally comfortable guiding people=\r\n in jnaana, vedanta, Raama bhakti, Krishna bhakti, Kaali bhakti, Shiva bhak=\r\nti, karma yoga, service, hatha yoga, tantra etc, having experienced all. He=\r\n even did smashana sadhanas, Islamic sadhanas and experienced Jesus Christ.=\r\n He is a unique teacher in the last few millennia. Many other masters take =\r\ndisciples on the path they walked. Having walked all paths to the summit, R=\r\namakrishna guided disciples on different paths based on their aptitude.&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\nThough upanishads and Bhagavad Gita are teaching Adwaita clearly, some gr=\r\neat masters came in the last few millennia who taught variations in the Upa=\r\nnishadic philosophy veering towards duality to various degrees. I think thi=\r\ns happened for a purpose. As true Adwaita as taught by Upanishads and Bhaga=\r\nvad Gita becomes more and more inappropriate and difficult for the masses, =\r\na simpler message that they can understand and that can guide their spiritu=\r\nal lives is needed. I think the coming of various masters who taught differ=\r\nent philosophies is for that reason.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=\r\n=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThe title of the mail was &quot;=\r\nFearlessness Comes In The Supreme State Of Non-duality&quot;. However, the =\r\nquestion is: Does non-duality bring fearlessness or vice versa?&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nA =\r\nrealization of non-dual Self may suddenly happen oneday for some rare perso=\r\nns. For most, it happens as a result of sadhana done over many years/lives.=\r\n Thus, qualities like dispassion, fearlessness (which are associated with t=\r\nhe supreme state) need to be cultivated actively. As they become more and m=\r\nore perfected, one gets closer and closer to Self-realization.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nS=\r\nuppose one sees a beautiful/ugly object (or a desirable/undesirable object)=\r\n. When one feels attraction/aversion, one should remind oneself &quot;all i=\r\ns god (Self). There is no need for feeling attraction/aversion towards anyt=\r\nhing.&quot; When one feels fear, one should remind oneself &quot;all is god=\r\n (Self). There is no need for be afraid of *anything*&quot;. As one practic=\r\nes this, one&#39;s dispassion and fearlessness increase. Incidents of delus=\r\nion becomes smaller and less frequent. Eventually, one overcomes.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\nBut the tricky part is that one needs to perform the actions one is meant=\r\n to perform and work out the kaarmik debts, before one realizes Self. It is=\r\n very difficult to perform actions without feeling even small amounts of at=\r\ntachment, attraction, aversion, passion, fear etc.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nA simple form=\r\nula is: Give all you can and expect nothing (and accept whatever you get) i=\r\nn return. In the beginning, any attraction/aversion/anxiety/fear you feel s=\r\nhould be with regard to what are giving to others and not with regard to wh=\r\nat you are expecting from others.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*=\r\n =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIt is all easy to write and read the=\r\nory. The problem comes when one is tested in real life. For example, I chok=\r\ned when eating something once when I was alone and could not breathe. I bec=\r\name anxious and it made it worse. Suddenly, the thought came to me &quot;wh=\r\nat are you afraid of? Death? This will mostly result in a little suffering =\r\nfor a couple of minutes and no more. EVEN IF it results in death, what is t=\r\nhe big deal? Jaatasya dhruvam mrityuh (each being who is born is sure of de=\r\natth). Is there anything I wanted to do and could not do? Well, there may b=\r\ne, but someone else can do it. Why should only Narasimha do it? World will =\r\nrun perfectly fine even if I am not here. If I indeed die now, why don&#39;=\r\nt I meditate and focus my mind on god, instead of focusing on my life and g=\r\netting anxious?&quot; I relaxed and meditated for a few minutes with Gayatr=\r\ni mantra. My anxiety went away and I felt nice after a while.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nAs=\r\n one detects and actively suppresses undesirable thoughts more and more, su=\r\nch thoughts will become less and less frequent and eventually be suppressed=\r\n by the mind even in the seed/formatory state. Later, causes of those seeds=\r\n themselves will be wiped out from the sub-conscious mind. This is how cond=\r\nitioning of the mind is slowly overcome. It is certainly a long process for=\r\n most of us, but one loses nothing by starting and trying to make progress.=\r\n Sadhanas like homam and japam aid one in this.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nPlease note that=\r\n even Ramana maharshi and Ramakrishna Paramahamsa did intense sadhana for m=\r\nany years, before they could reach the supreme state. No matter who you are=\r\n, some sadhana is needed.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =\r\n=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWhile on the topic of Adwaita, I want to mak=\r\ne one more point. It poses two dangers. While the Ultimate Reality is indee=\r\nd non-dual, *half-baked* understanding of Adwaita philosophy can make one *=\r\ntrivialize* duality on one extreme or *glorify* ignorance on the other extr=\r\neme. Let me explain.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nReading that the ultimate reality behind al=\r\nl that we see is the non-dual Self can make some people trivialize the dual=\r\nity that we normally experience. If duality is &quot;mithya&quot; (an illus=\r\nion), how does it matter and how do our actions within it matter? It is all=\r\n, after all, an illusion.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nOf course, a true student of vedanta w=\r\nill know that the layer of illusion is quite important and cannot be ignore=\r\nd simply because it is an &quot;illusion&quot;. If one&#39;s consciousness =\r\nis veiled by the layer of illusion, actions within that layer of illusion a=\r\nre required for removing it. It will not magically disappear. After all, yo=\r\nga vaasishtham emphasizes &quot;actions&quot; in the dual world for realizi=\r\nng non-dual Self. Action and knowledge as the two wings with which the bird=\r\n of individualized consciousness rises from the ground of duality to reach =\r\nthe sky of true Self.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nOn the other extreme,&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =\r\n=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nEnough for now.=\r\n I have not gone anywhere and still reading the list regularly. But I did n=\r\not have motivation to reply to any recent mails. Basically, if I have no us=\r\neful or meaningful comment/reply, I keep quiet.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIntellectual excha=\r\nnges are interesting, but the thing that matters at the end of the day is w=\r\nhether we are doing sincere sadhana or not and whether we are progressing o=\r\nr not. It seems to me like several people are sincerely doing homam/japam a=\r\nnd sincerely trying to make progress. Several more people are about to do t=\r\nhe same. THAT is what really matters. What we think or say about the world,=\r\n duality and non-duality is irrelevant really. What matters is whether our =\r\nattitude is changing for the better.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=\r\n=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nLet me give one more quick analo=\r\ngy before I stop for now.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSuppose one is sleeping and seeing an el=\r\naborate dream. Suppose one is fully absorbed in the dream and weeping in pa=\r\nin when something bad happens in the dream and laughing in elation when som=\r\nething good happens in the dream. One can tell that it is bad.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nS=\r\nuppose another person has read *in the dream* that what one is experiencing=\r\n is called a &quot;dream&quot; and will end soon and what happens in the dr=\r\neam is irrelevant. Suppose one intellectually understands all that and yet =\r\nweeps in pain when something bad happens in the dream and laughs in elation=\r\n when something good happens in the dream. Is that any better? Of course no=\r\nt.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nOn the other hand, if one is slowly getting control over the =\r\nmind and not weeping as often and not laughing as often, one is perhaps mak=\r\ning progress.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0* =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =\r\n=C2=A0*&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nDo whatever your conscience tells you to do. But expect no=\r\nthing in return and accept whatever comes to you as a result. As your accep=\r\ntance increases, the clarity with which your conscience shows you the path =\r\nyou should take (with regard to your actions) will become better and better=\r\n. If your actions were bad in the past (due to unclear guidelines from cons=\r\ncience or not following your conscience) and you are receiving bad fruits, =\r\nyou can still overcome it by learning to accept what comes. As your accepta=\r\nnce is perfected, your conscience and will power will become pure and your =\r\nactions will become pure. As actions become pure, newer fruits will be pure=\r\n. Eventually, you start making progress.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nBest regards,&lt;br&gt;\nNaras=\r\nimha&lt;br&gt;\n------------------------------------------------------------------=\r\n-&lt;br&gt;\n =C2=A0Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Ta=\r\nrpana:&lt;br&gt;\n =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0&lt;=\r\na href=3D&quot;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.Vedi=\r\ncAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n =C2=A0 =C2=A0 Films that make a difference: &lt;a hre=\r\nf=3D&quot;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://SaraswatiFilms.org=\r\n&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n =C2=A0 =C2=A0 Spirituality: &lt;a href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/gr=\r\noup/vedic-wisdom&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wis=\r\ndom&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n =C2=A0Jyotish writings: &lt;a href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/gro=\r\nup/JyotishWritings&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Jyotish=\r\nWritings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n----------------------------------------------------------=\r\n---------&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n---- Prasanth Jalasutram &lt;&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:jvrsprasa=\r\nnth@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;jvrsprasanth@...&lt;/a&gt;&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; =C2=A0Because of the ignorance of the mind experiencing a sense of dif=\r\nference&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; [bheda-buddhi] in Self, [even] great devas are disturbed b=\r\ny fear.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; [Therefore] it is wise to remain without fear in the supre=\r\nme state of&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; non-duality, having attained the reality, one=E2=80=99=\r\ns own Self, through negation&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; [of the non-Self].&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nSadhu Om: The nature of jiva is to think that fear will be removed only whe=\r\nn&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; there is some other person with him. But this idea is foolish. H=\r\now can there&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; be cause for fear in the state of Self, where no othe=\r\nr thing exists?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Only in a state where there exists someth=\r\ning other than oneself is it&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; possible for one either to have desir=\r\ne for that thing or to have fear of it.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Therefore, true fearlessne=\r\nss can be attained only in the non-dual state of&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Self, where no ot=\r\nher thing exists.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; To illustrate how fearlessness can be a=\r\nttained only when one attains the&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; state of Self, Sri Bhagavan used=\r\n to narrate the following story:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; After Lord Vishnu had ki=\r\nlled Hiranya, Hiranya=E2=80=99s son Prahlada was happily&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ruling th=\r\ne kingdom.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; But after some time, a fear arose in Prahlada.=\r\n =E2=80=9CBecause Lord Vishnu is kind&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to me, I am living safely. B=\r\nut if one day He becomes angry with me, He will&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; kill me just as He=\r\n killed my father,=E2=80=9D thought Prahlada.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Being a gre=\r\nat devotee of Lord Vishnu, Prahlada had no one else to turn to,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; so=\r\n he&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; prayed to Him. The Lord immediately appeared before Prahlada,w=\r\nho then&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; explained his fear and prayed for the state of fearlessnes=\r\ns.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =E2=80=9CYes,=E2=80=9D said Lord Vishnu, =E2=80=9CYou =\r\nare correct. By seeing me like this in name&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; and form, you cannot b=\r\ne free from fear.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; You must see me within yourself. Only w=\r\nhen you thus realize me to be not&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; different from yourself, will yo=\r\nu attain the state of fearlessness=E2=80=9D. Then&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; the Lord taught =\r\nhim the path of Self-enquiry. When Prahlada followed the&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Lord=E2=\r\n=80=99s instructions and realized Self, he attained the state of&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; f=\r\nearlessness.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; This story thus illustrates that even God ca=\r\nnnot serve as permanent refuge&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; from fear so long as one retains th=\r\ne sense of difference [bheda-buddhi].&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Only by attaining the non-du=\r\nal Self can one become truly and permanently&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; free from fear.&lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Source: GURU VACHAKA KOVAI The Light of Supreme Truth or THE C=\r\nOLLECTION OF&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; GURU=E2=80=99S SAYINGS translated from original Tamil=\r\n By Sadhu Om and Michael James&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Guru Vachaka Kovai is the =\r\nbiggest collection of Bhagavan=E2=80=99s spoken teachings&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; that was=\r\n thoroughly checked and revised by him during his lifetime. As such&lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; it has a unique place in the Ramana literature.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; --&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; ?? =C2=A0??? =C2=A0????? =C2=A0???? =C2=A0?????&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ???????? =C2=\r\n=A0????????&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ?????? ????????&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br cl=\r\near=3D&quot;all&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;all&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;-- =\r\n&lt;br&gt;=E0=B0=93=E0=B0=82 =C2=A0=E0=B0=A8=E0=B0=AE=E0=B1=8B =C2=A0=E0=B0=AD=E0=\r\n=B0=97=E0=B0=B5=E0=B0=A4=E0=B1=87 =C2=A0=E0=B0=B6=E0=B1=8D=E0=B0=B0=E0=B1=\r\n=80 =C2=A0=E0=B0=B0=E0=B0=AE=E0=B0=A3=E0=B0=BE=E0=B0=AF =C2=A0 &lt;br&gt;=E0=B0=\r\n=AA=E0=B1=8D=E0=B0=B0=E0=B0=B6=E0=B0=BE=E0=B0=82=E0=B0=A4=E0=B1=8D =C2=A0=\r\n=E0=B0=9C=E0=B0=B2=E0=B0=B8=E0=B1=82=E0=B0=A4=E0=B1=8D=E0=B0=B0=E0=B0=82 &lt;b=\r\nr&gt;=E0=B0=AA=E0=B1=8D=E0=B0=B0=E0=B1=87=E0=B0=AE=E0=B1=87 =E0=B0=B6=E0=B0=BE=\r\n=E0=B0=B6=E0=B1=8D=E0=B0=B5=E0=B0=